01/07/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Sixteen illegal migrants drowned while attempting to enter Greece via the Evros River at the Turkish border, police announced on Wednesday (June 30th). All of victims were of African and Asian origin. Police say they were part of a bigger group that crossed the river on June 25th. The Turkish smugglers ferried the children by boat but told the adults to swim. (DPA, Reuters - 30/06/10)
